-- =============================================
-- PEDAGOGICAL DESIGN
-- =============================================

-- NULL handling (Phone)
--   Patients 3, 6, 11, 12 have NULL phone numbers
--   Enables IS NULL / IS NOT NULL exercises

-- NULL handling (Email)
--   Email is NOT NULL in this dataset

-- Status filtering
--   Status values: Active, Inactive, Admitted
--   Enables =, !=, and IN exercises

-- Category filtering
--   Categories: Cardiology, Neurology, Surgery, Primary Care, Diagnostic,
--               Surgical, Rehabilitation, Pharmacy, Preventative
--   Enables category-based filtering exercises

-- Comparison Operators (>, >=, <, <=, =, <>)
--   Cost: 25, 45, 75, 85, 120, 350, 550, 850, 1200, 1600, 1800, 2200, 2500, 4500
--   Amount: 25, 45, 75, 85, 120, 350, 550, 850, 1200, 6000
--   Enables >, >=, <, <=, =, <> exercises

-- BETWEEN (Date Range)
--   Appointments and bills spread across Jan–May 2025
--   Enables BETWEEN date range exercises

-- LIKE / Pattern Matching
--   Names: John, Emma, Michael, Sarah, James, Maria, Robert, Patricia, David, Linda, Thomas, Anna, Elizabeth
--   Enables LIKE with '%', '_', starts with, ends with
--   LIKE '%th' returns at least 2 rows (John Smith, Elizabeth)

-- Aliases
--   Column names: name, email, phone, status, treatment_name, cost, category, etc.
--   Enables AS alias exercises

-- JOINs
--   Patients, appointments, treatments, and bills enable multi-table JOIN exercises
--   appointments now has treatment_id FK → enables JOIN between appointments and treatments

-- Aggregation (Group By / Having)
--   Multiple bills per patient → supports SUM, AVG, COUNT, GROUP BY
--   Multiple appointments per patient → supports COUNT, GROUP BY
--   Multiple appointments per treatment category → supports GROUP BY category

-- Edge Cases
--   Patients 4 and 8 have status 'Inactive' → supports NOT / != filtering
--   Patients 11 and 12 have status 'Admitted' → supports = filtering
--   Bills 13 (25.00) and 14 (6000.00) are outliers → supports < 50 OR > 5000
--   Bills 5 and 15 fall within March 1-7 → supports BETWEEN date range

